The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 21 (PTI): Migrating Indian workers will be trained before their departure by the government to upgrade their skills and orientation.           der the programme for 2008-2010, workers will be trained mandatorily and free of charge for 15 days to three months in the trade they will take up abroad, and in the laws and culture of the country they will be going to.                  
	 Hyderabad (PTI): An eight-month-old boy died after his father allegedly threw him on the floor, police said on Sunday. K. Sudarshan had a tiff with wife Vijaylakshmi, when he snatched the baby from her and hurled him on the floor. Sudarshan, who was allegedly drunk when the incident happened, has been booked under Section 304 (Culpable homicide not amounting to murder) of the IPC.                  
	 Panaji (PTI): Goa chief minister Digambar Kamat inaugurated the countrys first e-law library on Saturday. The library, he said, would serve as a model for other bar councils. The library would have an archive of judgments and lawyers will be able to take printouts for reference.                  
	 Kuala Lumpur (PTI): A party of ethnic Indians in Malaysia on Sunday appealed to the Abdullah Badawi government to immediately release five leaders of a Hindu group detained since last December for organising a rally to protest racial inequality.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): Police foiled a blast on Sunday with the recovery of five grenades in Jammu city. Some children had told the police that a bag in a gutter near Bahu Fort contained explosives. Army troops recovered a live grenade in a field in a bordering village.                  
	 Vadodara (PTI): The Pakistani marine security agency arrested 13 Indian fishermen on Saturday and seized their boats from the Jakhau waters in the Arabian Sea. The fishermen have been lodged in a jail in Karachi, a fishermens forum said.                                                                                                                         
